Wash and dry produce.

Quarter @lime{1}. Finely dice @roma tomato{1}.

Peel and finely dice @kiwi{1}. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1}; mince
a few slices until you have 2 TBSP (3 TBSP for 4 servings). Roughly chop
@cilantro{1/4%oz}. Core, deseed, and finely chop @long green pepper{1}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{4%tbsp} with a squeeze of lime juice. Add
@water{1%tsp} at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

In a #medium bowl{}, toss together tomato, kiwi, minced onion, half the
cilantro, and a squeeze of lime juice. Season with salt and pepper.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{4%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat.
Add sliced onion, green pepper, and half the @Southwest spice blend{1%tbsp} (you'll use
the rest in the next step). Cook, stirring occasionally, until softened and lightly
charred, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add a large drizzle of oil, @chicken breast strips{10%oz}, and remaining Southwest
spice blend to pan with veggies. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned
and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

> Swap in beef or chicken for pork (no need to break up chicken into pieces!).

Reduce heat under pan to medium low.

> TIP: If there's excess grease in your pan, carefully pour it out.

Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @tomato paste{1.5%oz}, and @water{1/4%cup} (1/3
cup for 4 servings). Cook, stirring, until everything is coated in a thick sauce,
~{1-2%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp paper towels and microwave until warm and pliable,
~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between plates and fill with pork filling, salsa, and crema.
Sprinkle with remaining cilantro. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.